  "body": "\r\n**1. Report a `bug`**  \r\n\r\n**2. `findDOMNode` does not work on `StatelessComponent`**\r\n\r\n**3. Detail**\r\nHello, I need to hide a component in its parent `A`( `A` is parent, `B` is child), while `B` is writen by others and i can't rewrite any code in it.  \r\n`findDOMNode` can resolve this problems , but it seems useless on `StatelessComponent`, so how can i resolve it?  \r\nHere is my code, thanks a lot.\r\n```\r\nclass A extends React.Component {\r\n\r\n  componentDidMount() {\r\n    findDOMNode(this.refs.b2).style.display = 'none'\r\n  }\r\n\r\n  render() {\r\n    return (\r\n      <div>\r\n        <B ref='b1'/>\r\n        <B ref='b2'/>\r\n      </div>\r\n    )\r\n  }\r\n}\r\n\r\nconst B = ()=> {\r\n  return <div>Page B</div>\r\n}\r\n```\r\n",
